Class VectorArray<V extends Vec>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<V>
          • jsat.linear.vectorcollection.VectorArray<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<V>, java.util.Collection<V>, java.util.List<V>, java.util.RandomAccess, VectorCollection<V>

    public class VectorArray<V extends Vec>
extends java.util.ArrayList<V>
implements VectorCollection<V>
    This is the naive implementation of a Vector collection. Construction time is O(n) only to clone the n elements, and all queries are O(n2)
